- INSTALL Instructions

Linux

Install the libssl-dev package.  Run `make` in the src directory.  Copy the binaries to a common path (i.e. /usr/local/bin).

MacOS

Be sure Xcode is installed.  Install via Homebrew the openssl package.  Run `make` in the src directory.  Copy the binaries to a common path (i.e. /usr/local/bin).

FreeBSD

Change the first line of the makefile to CC=clang.  Run `make` in the src directory.  Copy the binaries to a common path (i.e. /usr/local/bin).

OpenBSD

Run `make` in the src directory.  Copy the binaries to a common path (i.e. /usr/local/bin).

Solaris

Run `make` in the src directory.  Copy the binaries to a common path (i.e. /usr/local/bin).

-- Optional

For a brand new install of Solaris 11.4, update the system by executing `pkg update --accept`.  Install openssl v3 `pkg install openssl-3`.
